data.description:
Two-story open foyer is the entrance to this 3287 square foot single family home with 4 bedrooms and 3.5 bathrooms.  Built in 2000, architectural ammenities include crown and chair rail decorative moldings, decorative columns leading to the formal dining room with tray ceiling, vaulted cathedral ceilings in the master bedroom which features a full master bath including both shower and garden tub behind glass french doors, and master suite fireplace with premium built in seating and drawers tastefully located so as not to interfere with bedroom furniture.  Vaulted ceilings in both the master bedroom and office/library/study, feature ceiling fans extending down from the peaks with light kits, and recessed lighting to set the right mood.
Study includes premium built-ins featuring cabinets, drawes, shelving, beverage/wine cooler, and wet bar.  Second floor guest bath features a jetted tub with shower fixture, and a double vanity/sinks.  Built in entertainment center in the family room will accomodate up to 75" TV.  In-ground salt water pool has paramount self cleaning in-floor cleaning system, three-tier waterfall with natural privacy backdrop, premium Pebble-Tec interior surface coating that requires no paint or liner, LED lighting, and pool bath/wash room w/shower accessible from the rear deck with non-slip ceramic tile floor for safety.  Two large garage bays at the front of this home are convenient to the open kitchen for easy handling of groceries.  A third garage entrance is located at the sideof the home, currently used for tractor and lanscaping tool storage, and workshop.  
 It is located at 21 Dickinson Dr Hanover, Pennsylvania. This home is in the Conewago Valley School District. The nearest schools are Conewago Township, New Oxford and New Oxford.
